&lt;p&gt;This article mainly introduces the use of Emoji in the Hugo framework, adding cute emoji to your blog posts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;method-to-realize&#34; &gt;Method to realize
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#method-to-realize&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Displaying Emoji in the article can directly call the &lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/functions/emojify/&#34;&gt;emojify&lt;/a&gt; function and use the [Inline Shortcodes](&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/templates/shortcode-templates/#inline-&#34;&gt;https://gohugo.io/templates/shortcode-templates/#inline-&lt;/a&gt; shortcodes) function implementation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;p.s.: After opening InlineShortcodes, it will have many powerful functions, such as inserting YouTube videos, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is just a chance to enjoy Jinyoung&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;Dive&amp;rdquo; with you~~&lt;/p&gt;

